4 Pillars of OOP

-Polymorphism: the ability to reuse and redefine the same method throughout multiple
               classes.

-Inheritance: the ability to define a class that inherits the methodds and properties
              from another class.
              Parent Class ---> Child Class

-Abstraction: the concept where the user is kept unaware of what goes on in the
              implementation the function property.

-Encapsulation: the concept of capturing the data and methods that work together
                within one unit.